text: Mike Sewak is a former American football player and coach. He served as the head football coach at Georgia Southern University from 2002 to 2005, compiling a record of 35–14. He retired after the 2018 season as an assistant coach at the Georgia Institute of Technology. ==Head coaching record== ==References== Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Living people Category:American football offensive linemen Category:Georgia Southern Eagles football coaches Category:Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets football coaches Category:Hawaii Rainbow Warriors football coaches Category:Hobart Statesmen football coaches Category:Ohio Bobcats football coaches Category:Virginia Cavaliers football players
